{
  "texts": [
    "The trace catalogue lists these values by the station for which the event has been triggered.",
    "Reference event and trace (metadata) catalogues for the WIS region during the 2010-2011 austral summer include stations triggered per event, network time, duration, amplitude, and energy (https://github.com/beccalatto/ multi_sta_lta/, last access: 18 March 2024).",
    "Events are first assigned high-or low-confidence labels based on the number of adjacent detecting stations (https: //github.com/beccalatto/multi_sta_lta/ provides documentation and corresponding assignments for the reference event catalogue).",
    "We find that approximately 35 % of events are categorized as high confidence (Table S2 in the Supplement).",
    "We choose to include all events (i.e., high and low confidence) in this analysis because the low-confidence event trends are generally consistent with those of high-confidence events (Sect. 3.3 and 3.4)."
  ]
}